title: Bug 121170: get_column_label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
OB: When calling the get_column_label function on the meta data object, the labels returned are null. However, after extraction, the labels should be recognizable strings.
EB: The get_column_label function should return user recognizable strings before extraction, similar to the labels obtained after extraction.
SR:
1. Create a meta data object.
2. Call the get_column_label function on the meta data object.
3. Verify that the returned labels are null.
4. Perform an extraction on the meta data object.
5. Call the get_column_label function on the extracted meta data object.
6. Verify that the returned labels are recognizable strings.
